North American Communications Corpsaid it is considering several options to maximize shareholdervalue, including a possible sale, merger, corporaterestructuring, or leveraged buyout.    Trading in the company's stock was halted pending anannouncement.    The company, which owns and operates 47 cable televisionsystems in Minnesota and Wisconsin, said it retainedCommunications Equity Associates as its financial adviser toexplore alternatives.    Reuter&#3;